        [
          "A former haunt and scare actor that wants something more from their after life.",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "Logan Boese"
        ],
        [
          "Staff Generated History"
        ],
        [
          "As a mortal, their life didn't amount to much. A string of dead end jobs and a constant yearning for something more. An Angeleno Born and Bred, they were never star struck by the glitz and glam of Hollywood, and being an actor was always just thought of as another potential career choice that didn't hold much allure for them. But, after a string of Getting By jobs lead them right back to where they started, a friend's recommendation got them a job as a Scare Actor at one of the prominent Haunted Attractions in the Region. Though they went into it without much expectation, the first Good Scare they got out of a person hooked them as strongly as any drug. They were amazing at it, and they found themselves Craving it. Every year, when the season ended they would focus only on what it would take to make themselves quieter next year. To make themselves Scarier. Of course, as with most addictions, there comes a point at which the same amount won't cure the craving any longer. They took to scaring Off-season as well. From quick, guerilla pop-scares to elaborately detailed pranks, they recorded themselves scaring absolutely everyone they could, (And the revenue from the videos after they were posted provided a tidy profit) They were good at their craft, and the ultimate acknowledgement of that came when they scared what appeared to be a handsome young man so badly, that his Obfuscate failed, revealing the horrid face of the Nosferatu underneath. They escaped that night, but found themselves face to face again with the horrid sight a week later, after the Nosferatu had appealed to the prince for the right to embrace a Childe. They adjusted well enough to the loss of their face and, after an adjustment period, realized that this was a Golden Opportunity. They now had all year to refine being as Scary as possible, and more than permission, they had Encouragement. They also found that their time in the Haunt had made them one of the Stealthiest even among the Sewer Rats. Coupled with their new vampiric prowess, they had a chance to really make something of themselves. The chance to refine that Stealth, and to put it to use against the enemies of their new Family, Clan, and Sect. They have all the tools and the raw potential of being interrogator and spy both, and now even the time to refine their abilities to their absolute peak, and they don't intend to waste them. They never amounted to much in their life, they don't intend to do the same with their unlife."
        ],
